 Scolari fined
Lisbon: Portugal coach Luiz Felipe Scolari has been fined $49,990 for lashing out at Serbia player Ivica Dragutinovic at the end of last months Euro 2008 qualifier, the Portuguese Soccer Federation said on Friday. The decision came after the appeals body at European soccers governing body Uefa effectively reduced the Brazilian coachs ban from four matches to three after he apologised for his assault on the Serb. (Reuters) 
